# tinji ui

tinji ui is a copy/paste component library built on **Base UI** (https://base-ui.com) and **Tailwind CSS v4**. It is shadcn-compatible but uses Base UI primitives, NOT Radix. Docs: https://ui.tinji.dev. Full LLM docs: https://ui.tinji.dev/llms-full.txt.

## Install

```bash
# add one component (JSON URL form)
npx shadcn@latest add https://ui.tinji.dev/r/<name>.json
# or via the registry namespace
npx shadcn@latest add @tinji/<name>
# all primitives
npx shadcn@latest add @tinji/ui
# new project: full theme + fonts
npx shadcn@latest init @tinji/style
```

Discover/inspect before adding: `npx shadcn@latest view @tinji/<name>`, `--dry-run`, `--diff`.

## Imports

- App-local (shadcn alias): `import { Button } from "@/components/ui/<name>"`
- Monorepo package: `import { Button } from "@tinji/ui/components/<name>"`
- Prefer the styled export. Use the `*Primitive` export only when you need custom composition/styling: `import { Slider, SliderPrimitive } from "@tinji/ui/components/slider"`.
- Need Base UI utils? Import via tinji to avoid a direct `@base-ui/react` dep: `@tinji/ui/base-ui/{use-render,merge-props,csp-provider,direction-provider}`.
- Icons: named imports from `lucide-react` only.

## Base UI conventions (NOT Radix)

- **`render` prop, never `asChild`.** Compose elements with `render`:
  ```tsx
  <MenuTrigger render={<Button variant="outline" />}>Open</MenuTrigger>
  <Button render={<Link href="/login" />}>Login</Button>
  ```
- **Popup/Panel naming**, not `*Content`:
  - Overlays expose `*Popup` (`DialogPopup`, `MenuPopup`, `SelectPopup`, `PopoverPopup`).
  - `Dialog`/`Sheet`/`Drawer` also have `*Panel` for the scrollable body and `*Header`/`*Footer`.
- **Menu items use `onClick`**, not `onSelect`. Add `closeOnClick` to close on activation.
- **Toggle/checkbox groups:** `multiple={true}` (not Radix `type="multiple"`).
- **`portalProps`** on supported `*Popup` surfaces and toast providers takes Base UI portal options (`keepMounted`, `container`) instead of a manual portal tree.

## Select is items-first

Pass `items` to `<Select>`; map them in `SelectPopup`. `SelectValue` needs no `placeholder` child.

```tsx
const items = [
  { label: "Select…", value: null },
  { label: "Next.js", value: "next" },
];
<Select items={items}>
  <SelectTrigger><SelectValue /></SelectTrigger>
  <SelectPopup>
    {items.map((i) => (
      <SelectItem key={String(i.value)} value={i}>{i.label}</SelectItem>
    ))}
  </SelectPopup>
</Select>
```

## Toasts use `toastManager` (NOT Sonner)

Wrap the app in `ToastProvider` (or `AnchoredToastProvider`), then:

```tsx
import { toastManager } from "@/components/ui/toast";
toastManager.add({ title: "Saved", description: "…", type: "success" });
```

Pass a stable `id` on `add` to update an existing toast in place instead of stacking a duplicate.

## Composition

- **Dialog/Sheet/Drawer:** `*Trigger` → `*Popup` containing `*Header` (`*Title`/`*Description`), `*Panel`, `*Footer`. For forms, keep the header OUTSIDE `<Form>` and wrap `*Panel` + `*Footer` in `<Form className="contents">`.
- **Group:** put a `<GroupSeparator />` between every control (required, even between outline buttons).
- **InputGroup:** `InputGroupAddon` must come AFTER the `InputGroupInput`/`InputGroupTextarea` in DOM order (focus relies on it); use `align` for visual position.

## Accessibility

- Icon-only interactive element → `aria-label` on it, `aria-hidden="true"` on the icon. Prefer `aria-label` over `sr-only` text.
- Decorative icons (in buttons, badges, menu items, input addons) → `aria-hidden="true"`. Do NOT add opacity classes to icons inside buttons.
- Semantic icons (Alert severity) → do NOT add `aria-hidden`.
- Always set an explicit `type` on `Input`/`InputGroupInput` (`text`, `email`, `search`, …).
- Wrap a checkbox/radio/switch and its text in `<Label>`; only use `id`/`htmlFor` when extra (description) content sits outside the label.
- Use `Field` (`FieldLabel`, `FieldError`) for form structure.

## Styling

- Semantic tokens only: `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-destructive` — never raw `text-gray-500`.
- `border-border` is the default; just use `border`/`border-b`.
- Prefer `in-[[data-slot=button]:hover]:…` over the `group`/`group-hover:` pattern.
- Use the `!` suffix for important overrides (`h-auto!`).
- Extra tokens to import when installing manually: `--destructive-foreground`, `--info(-foreground)`, `--success(-foreground)`, `--warning(-foreground)`. The CLI wires these automatically.

## Rules of thumb

1. Use existing tinji primitives/particles before writing custom markup.
2. Verify component APIs against the docs; do not invent props.
3. Don't mix Radix patterns (`asChild`, `*Content`, `onSelect`) into tinji.
4. Browse ready-made examples ("particles") at https://ui.tinji.dev/particles (install via `https://ui.tinji.dev/r/<particle-name>.json`).
